        "creation_date": 1502353150,
        "body": "<p>Of course you can (insofar that compilation will pass), although you will probably not get the result you expect since using <code>==<\/code> will compare <em>references<\/em> <strong>not<\/strong> <em>contents<\/em>.<\/p>\n\n<p>My favourite way is to use the <em>Yoda Expression<\/em> <code>\"\".equals(myString)<\/code> since then you don't need to pre-test <code>myString<\/code> for <code>null<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>Else you could use <code>myString.isEmpty()<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 45608139,
        "question_id": 45608094,
        "last_edit_date": 1502353574
    }],
